    {
      "id": "1007616115759880",
      "score": 3,
      "review_title": "Limited appeal. Gets boring quick.",
      "review_description": "If you ever wanted to hack and slash enemies that enter into your own home, this can be fun. The mixed-reality allows you to see the room you are in, but enhances it so it looks like you are in some medieval fantasy world. Enemies enter through your doors and windows, and you have to battle them. It's kinda fun, but the graphics of the enemies is a bit lame. It is a neat example of mixed reality gaming, but that's about as far as it goes.\n\nThe enemies are repetitive, as is the game play. You'd think it could be easy enough to add a few different heads/faces or even body types to change things up. But no, it's the same guys, over and over again.  I suppose , for a bit of variety, you can start Survival mode in a different room, but other than that, it's pretty much the same thing.  More game modes or dynamic situations or changing scenes or some story modes, might have helped. \n\nIt gets tired rather quick, but can be nice for trying out mixed reality. I hope the devs can take some decent basics and improve this game with some updates. It could be more fun.\n\nHEY DEVS, look at all the comments about 1) people having problems with locating the crystal, 2) people \"not in the room\", 3) can't start the game. It might be nice to respond to these. Showing you care to address concerns and provide updates might actually get you more positive ratings and sales.",
      "date": 1768867366,
      "review_helpful_count": 14,
      "author_display_name": "AstroKQ",
      "author_alias": "AstroKQ",
      "developer_response": null
    },
